# Time Complexity and big O notation

            the amount of amount of work which is done by the program while increasing the size of the input size is known as time complexity 
            big O notation denotes the different types of time complexity 

# Types of time complexity 

            O(1) = this is used when the amount of work done by the program is constant regardless of the input size 
            O(n) = this is used when the amount of work done by the program is increasing linearly with respect to the increase in the size of the input 
            O(n^2) = this is used when we are using the nested loops 

# Rules of time complexity 

